<h2>Our Methodology &amp; Standards</h2>
<div class="methodology-grid">
<div class="method-card">
<h3>Court-Ready Analysis</h3>
<p>All analyses follow accepted economic principles and methodologies that meet court standards for expert testimony admissibility.</p>
</div>
<div class="method-card">
<h3>Current Data Sources</h3>
<p>We utilize the most current economic data from Bureau of Labor Statistics, Census Bureau, and Federal Reserve sources.</p>
</div>
<div class="method-card">
<h3>Peer Review Standards</h3>
<p>Our methodologies are consistent with those published in peer-reviewed economics journals and professional practice standards.</p>
</div>
<div class="method-card">
<h3>Clear Communication</h3>
<p>Complex economic concepts are explained clearly for judges and juries, with compelling visual presentations.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
